So if I need to reopen and re-resolve them let me know.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14523012" author="hcorg" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 10:22:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jfarrell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jfarrell&quot;&gt;jfarrell&lt;/a&gt; said so than ok, my bad. I was just used to him doing it &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14523203" author="jfarrell" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 13:41:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The release notes are generated from the tickets fix version, so does not matter if they are resolved and someone bulk sets the fix version and closes or if they are just closed with that all ready set. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The other thing to make sure of is that the person who has done the work on the ticket is set as the asignee, that way the merit for the ticket can be recorded and we can look it up easier later on (say when considering a new committer)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14523246" author="hcorg" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 14:27:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;and assignee cannot be changed on closed issue, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jking3&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jking3&quot;&gt;jking3&lt;/a&gt; was not in proper Jira group yesterday yet (not every Jira user can be assignee).&lt;br/&gt;
So I &lt;b&gt;did&lt;/b&gt; remember it&apos;s important to leave resolved issue for a while &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14523250" author="jking3" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 14:30:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, I will go through all the issues in the last few weeks I closed and reopen/reassign/re-resolve them.  I like to clear issues off the radar since there are usually so many, which is why I closed them.  If the preference is to leave them resolved instead of closed I will do that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14523694" author="jensg" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 18:58:47 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;not every Jira user can be assignee&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s something that actually blocks the workflow a good deal. I found myself frequently trying to assign the right assignee only to find out tzhat I can&apos;t assign them 90% of the time. At some point is stopped doing this and instead started assingning it to myself whenever I commit something. Maybe that&apos;s not perfectly right, but at least 50% because I reviewed and committed the patch. Works every time I try and is just one click away!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bottom line:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I wonder what the reason for this restriction is after all, and/or&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;what I can do to overcome that easily (i.e. within seconds)?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14523697" author="jensg" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 18:59:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;read: &quot;... Ast some point I stopped ...&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14524502" author="henrique" created="Sat, 2 May 2015 02:56:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As Jens said, most users cannot be assigned and it seemed like the assignee field was been used as a synchronisation point so we&apos;d now that someone is already reviewing/committing that patch. This works quite well IMHO.&lt;br/&gt;
Although it&apos;d be just fair to assign it to the contributor, their activity also reflects on the email volume, as Jake had already used a couple of times.&lt;br/&gt;
An alternative would be to try to assign it again to the contributor before resolving it, or use another field for the committers...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14524520" author="jfarrell" created="Sat, 2 May 2015 03:40:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All committers and pmc members have the ability to add new people to the contributor role within our jira project, not as easy as 1 click away, but not a limiting factor either&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
